{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FbHZzkEoUdAR5DM2inhmbN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * SessionContext — JWT session management for wallet authentication.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Provides sign-once authentication: wallet signs a human-readable challenge\n     5→ * on connect, backend issues JWT access + refresh tokens, and all subsequent\n     6→ * requests use Bearer tokens.\n     7→ */\n     8→\n     9→import {\n    10→  createContext,\n    11→  useContext,\n    12→  useState,\n    13→  useCallback,\n    14→  useEffect,\n    15→  useRef,\n    16→  type ReactNode,\n    17→} from \"react\";\n    18→import bs58 from \"bs58\";\n    19→import { useWallet } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks\";\n    20→import {\n    21→  requestChallenge,\n    22→  verifyChallenge,\n    23→  refreshSession,\n    24→  logout,\n    25→} from \"../lib/auth-api\";\n    26→import {\n    27→  getAccessToken,\n    28→  setAccessToken,\n    29→  getPersistedSession,\n    30→  setPersistedSession,\n    31→  clearPersistedSession,\n    32→  getAccessExpiresAt,\n    33→} from \"../lib/auth-store\";\n    34→\n    35→interface SessionContextValue {\n    36→  isAuthenticated: boolean;\n    37→  isAuthenticating: boolean;\n    38→  accessToken: string | null;\n    39→  authenticate: () => Promise<string>;\n    40→  clearSession: () => void;\n    41→}\n    42→\n    43→const SessionContext = createContext<SessionContextValue | null>(null);\n    44→\n    45→export function SessionProvider({ children }: { children: ReactNode }) {\n    46→  const { connected, publicKey, signMessage } = useWallet();\n    47→\n    48→  const [isAuthenticated, setIsAuthenticated] = useState(false);\n    49→  const [isAuthenticating, setIsAuthenticating] = useState(false);\n    50→\n    51→  // Mutex for refresh — only one in-flight refresh at a time\n    52→  const refreshPromiseRef = useRef<Promise<boolean> | null>(null);\n    53→  const refreshTimerRef = useRef<number | null>(null);\n    54→  const prevWalletRef = useRef<string | null>(null);\n    55→\n    56→  const clearSession = useCallback(() => {\n    57→    const session = getPersistedSession();\n    58→    if (session) {\n    59→      // Best-effort logout on backend\n    60→      logout(session.refreshToken).catch(() => {});\n    61→    }\n    62→    clearPersistedSession();\n    63→    setIsAuthenticated(false);\n    64→    if (refreshTimerRef.current !== null) {\n    65→      clearTimeout(refreshTimerRef.current);\n    66→      refreshTimerRef.current = null;\n    67→    }\n    68→  }, []);\n    69→\n    70→  // Schedule proactive refresh ~5 min before access token expiry\n    71→  const scheduleRefresh = useCallback(() => {\n    72→    if (refreshTimerRef.current !== null) {\n    73→      clearTimeout(refreshTimerRef.current);\n    74→    }\n    75→\n    76→    const expiresAt = getAccessExpiresAt();\n    77→    if (!expiresAt) return;\n    78→\n    79→    const msUntilExpiry = new Date(expiresAt).getTime() - Date.now();\n    80→    // Refresh 5 minutes before expiry, or immediately if < 5 min remaining\n    81→    const refreshIn = Math.max(msUntilExpiry - 5 * 60 * 1000, 0);\n    82→\n    83→    refreshTimerRef.current = window.setTimeout(() => {\n    84→      refreshTimerRef.current = null;\n    85→      void tryRefresh();\n    86→    }, refreshIn);\n    87→  }, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n    88→\n    89→  const tryRefresh = useCallback(async (): Promise<boolean> => {\n    90→    // Mutex: if a refresh is already in-flight, await the same promise\n    91→    if (refreshPromiseRef.current) {\n    92→      return refreshPromiseRef.current;\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    const session = getPersistedSession();\n    96→    if (!session) return false;\n    97→\n    98→    const promise = (async () => {\n    99→      try {\n   100→        const result = await refreshSession(session.refreshToken);\n   101→        setAccessToken(result.accessToken, result.accessExpiresAt);\n   102→        setPersistedSession({\n   103→          wallet: session.wallet,\n   104→          cluster: session.cluster,\n   105→          refreshToken: result.refreshToken,\n   106→          refreshExpiresAt: result.refreshExpiresAt,\n   107→        });\n   108→        setIsAuthenticated(true);\n   109→        scheduleRefresh();\n   110→        return true;\n   111→      } catch {\n   112→        // Refresh failed — clear session\n   113→        clearPersistedSession();\n   114→        setIsAuthenticated(false);\n   115→        return false;\n   116→      } finally {\n   117→        refreshPromiseRef.current = null;\n   118→      }\n   119→    })();\n   120→\n   121→    refreshPromiseRef.current = promise;\n   122→    return promise;\n   123→  }, [scheduleRefresh]);\n   124→\n   125→  const authenticate = useCallback(async () => {\n   126→    if (!connected || !publicKey || !signMessage) {\n   127→      throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected or does not support message signing\");\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    setIsAuthenticating(true);\n   131→    try {\n   132→      const wallet = publicKey.toBase58();\n   133→\n   134→      // 1. Request challenge from backend\n   135→      const challenge = await requestChallenge(wallet);\n   136→\n   137→      // 2. Check challenge hasn't expired\n   138→      if (new Date(challenge.expiresAt).getTime() < Date.now()) {\n   139→        throw new Error(\"Challenge expired before signing\");\n   140→      }\n   141→\n   142→      // 3. Sign the human-readable message with wallet\n   143→      const messageBytes = new TextEncoder().encode(challenge.message);\n   144→      const signatureBytes = await signMessage(messageBytes);\n   145→      const signature = bs58.encode(signatureBytes);\n   146→\n   147→      // 4. Verify with backend — get tokens\n   148→      const result = await verifyChallenge(challenge.nonce, wallet, signature);\n   149→\n   150→      // 5. Store tokens\n   151→      setAccessToken(result.accessToken, result.accessExpiresAt);\n   152→      setPersistedSession({\n   153→        wallet,\n   154→        cluster: \"devnet\", // TODO: read from env\n   155→        refreshToken: result.refreshToken,\n   156→        refreshExpiresAt: result.refreshExpiresAt,\n   157→      });\n   158→\n   159→      setIsAuthenticated(true);\n   160→      scheduleRefresh();\n   161→      return result.accessToken;\n   162→    } catch (err) {\n   163→      // Clean up on failure\n   164→      clearPersistedSession();\n   165→      setIsAuthenticated(false);\n   166→      throw err;\n   167→    } finally {\n   168→      setIsAuthenticating(false);\n   169→    }\n   170→  }, [connected, publicKey, signMessage, scheduleRefresh]);\n   171→\n   172→  // Handle wallet connect: try to restore session or authenticate\n   173→  useEffect(() => {\n   174→    if (!connected || !publicKey) {\n   175→      // Wallet disconnected\n   176→      if (prevWalletRef.current !== null) {\n   177→        clearSession();\n   178→        prevWalletRef.current = null;\n   179→      }\n   180→      return;\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    const wallet = publicKey.toBase58();\n   184→\n   185→    // Wallet switched — clear old session first\n   186→    if (prevWalletRef.current !== null && prevWalletRef.current !== wallet) {\n   187→      clearSession();\n   188→    }\n   189→    prevWalletRef.current = wallet;\n   190→\n   191→    // Check for existing session\n   192→    const session = getPersistedSession();\n   193→    if (session && session.wallet === wallet) {\n   194→      // Try silent refresh\n   195→      const existingAccessToken = getAccessToken();\n   196→      if (existingAccessToken) {\n   197→        // Access token still valid\n   198→        setIsAuthenticated(true);\n   199→        scheduleRefresh();\n   200→        return;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MPoXotPwuktccSSbk63gaM","session_id":"69ec7f4b-ea2c-48d6-9a60-da2ab1703b1a","uuid":"018ddb9e-94b9-47ad-add5-d883b921d3d4"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a203ab741a0c3095b","tool_use_id":"toolu_01MPoXotPwuktccSSbk63gaM","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore coinflip wallet tx pattern","usage":{"total_tokens":82636,"tool_uses":30,"duration_ms":114521},"uuid":"3104c285-7df1-4b86-93ea-8265c47c098c","session_id":"69ec7f4b-ea2c-48d6-9a60-da2ab1703b1a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MPoXotPwuktccSSbk63gaM","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile a detailed technical report.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: Coinflip Wallet Transaction Building & Signing Pattern\n\nI've completed a very thorough analysis of how coinflip handles wallet transaction building, signing, and error handling. Here's the complete pattern you should replicate for closecall:\n\n---\n\n### **Architecture Overview**\n\nThe pattern follows **contract-first design**: transaction building is split between **backend (trust-critical)** and **frontend (UI/UX)**.\n\n**Key Files:**\n- **Backend TX building**: `utils/chain.ts` (`buildBackendCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, etc.)\n- **State management**: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx` (all transaction orchestration + error handling)\n- **Wallet integration**: `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` → `useWallet()` hook\n- **IDL definitions**: `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` → `CoinflipIDL` (read-only, pre-compiled)\n\n---\n\n### **1. Wallet Integration Pattern**\n\n#### The `useWallet()` Hook\nLocated: `/packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(WalletContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useWallet must be used within a WalletProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Returns** (`WalletContextValue`):\n```typescript\n{\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  getBalance?: () => number;        // mock mode only\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void;  // mock mode only\n}\n```\n\n#### Real Wallet Provider\nLocated: `/packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx`\n\nBridges `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` hooks to custom `WalletContext`:\n\n```typescript\nconst sendTransaction = useCallback(\n  async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n    if (!adapter.publicKey) {\n      throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n    }\n    const signature = await adapter.sendTransaction(transaction, connection);\n    return signature;\n  },\n  [adapter, connection],\n);\n```\n\n**Critical**: `sendTransaction` is a **direct pass-through** to the wallet adapter. It:\n- Does NOT sign transactions (wallet does that)\n- Does NOT set fee payers (caller does that)\n- Does NOT manage blockhashes (caller does that)\n- Simply returns the signature after broadcast\n\n---\n\n### **2. Transaction Building Pattern (Backend-First)**\n\n#### Create Match (Backend-Generated TX)\nLocation: `/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts:462`\n\n```typescript\nexport async function buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  amountSol: number,\n  side: CoinSide,\n  accessToken: string,\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey; commitment: string }> {\n  const payload = {\n    wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n    amountLamports: Math.round(amountSol * 1e9),\n    side: COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side],  // { heads: 0, tails: 1 }\n  };\n\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(), {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${accessToken}`,  // JWT from SessionContext\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n  });\n\n  const json = await parseBackendResponse<BackendCreateMatchResponse>(response);\n\n  return {\n    transaction: (() => {\n      const transaction = Transaction.from(Buffer.from(json.transaction, \"base64\"));\n      transaction.lastValidBlockHeight = json.lastValidBlockHeight;\n      return transaction;\n    })(),\n    matchPda: new PublicKey(json.matchPda),\n    commitment: json.commitment,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Backend constructs the raw transaction (contains all instructions)\n- Backend sends it **base64-encoded** with **pinned blockhash + lastValidBlockHeight**\n- Frontend decodes and reconstructs `Transaction` object\n- **Do NOT modify the transaction** — server already signed its parts\n- **Critical**: `transaction.lastValidBlockHeight` must be preserved (used later for confirmation logic)\n\n#### Join/Cancel/Timeout Refund (Frontend-Built TX)\nLocation: `/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts:498–574`\n\n```typescript\nexport async function buildJoinMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  opponent: PublicKey,\n  matchPda: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .joinMatch()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      opponent,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = opponent;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. Create `Program` instance using **read-only provider** (no wallet needed):\n   ```typescript\n   function getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n     const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n       connection,\n       {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n       { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n     );\n     return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. Build instruction via Anchor's `program.methods.<instruction>(args).accountsStrict({...}).instruction()`\n3. Create blank `Transaction()` and add the instruction\n4. Set `tx.feePayer = payer` (the account sending the tx)\n5. Fetch fresh blockhash and set `tx.recentBlockhash`\n6. Return (caller will sign + send)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Transaction Signing & Sending Pattern**\n\nLocated: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:186`\n\nThe **`sendAndConfirm` function** orchestrates the entire flow:\n\n```typescript\nconst sendAndConfirm = useCallback(\n  async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n    // (1) Detect if backend pre-signed the transaction\n    const hasPartialSignatures = transaction.signatures.some(\n      (entry) => entry.signature !== null\n    );\n    const preservesExternalSignature =\n      hasPartialSignatures &&\n      typeof transaction.recentBlockhash === \"string\";\n    const hasPinnedBlockhash =\n      preservesExternalSignature &&\n      typeof transaction.lastValidBlockHeight === \"number\";\n\n    if (preservesExternalSignature && !hasPinnedBlockhash) {\n      throw new Error(\n        \"Backend transaction is missing lastValidBlockHeight. Refusing to send with an incomplete confirmation contract.\",\n      );\n    }\n\n    // (2) Pre-flight simulation (unsigned, best-effort)\n    let cachedBlockhash: string | undefined;\n    let cachedHeight: number | undefined;\n    try {\n      if (!preservesExternalSignature) {\n        const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n          await connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\");\n        cachedBlockhash = blockhash;\n        cachedHeight = lastValidBlockHeight;\n        transaction.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\n      }\n\n      const simResult = await connection.simulateTransaction(transaction);\n      if (simResult.value.err) {\n        console.error(\"[coinflip] simulation failed BEFORE wallet send:\", \n          JSON.stringify(simResult.value.err));\n        if (simResult.value.logs) {\n          console.error(\"[coinflip] simulation logs:\\n\" + simResult.value.logs.join(\"\\n\"));\n        }\n        const err = simResult.value.err;\n        if (typeof err === \"object\" && err !== null && \"InstructionError\" in err) {\n          throw new Error(`Transaction will fail: ${JSON.stringify(err)}`);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (simErr) {\n      if (simErr instanceof Error && simErr.message.startsWith(\"Transaction will fail:\")) {\n        throw simErr;\n      }\n      console.error(\"[coinflip] simulation RPC error:\", simErr);\n    }\n\n    // (3) Send with retry logic (max 3 times for fresh TX, 1 time for backend TX)\n    const MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS = preservesExternalSignature ? 1 : 3;\n    for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS; attempt++) {\n      let blockhash: string;\n      let lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n      \n      if (preservesExternalSignature) {\n        // Reuse backend's pinned blockhash (already set in transaction)\n        blockhash = transaction.recentBlockhash!;\n        lastValidBlockHeight = transaction.lastValidBlockHeight ?? 0;\n      } else if (attempt === 1 && cachedBlockhash && cachedHeight) {\n        // Reuse simulation blockhash for first attempt (saves an RPC call)\n        blockhash = cachedBlockhash;\n        lastValidBlockHeight = cachedHeight;\n      } else {\n        // Fresh blockhash for retries\n        const fresh = await connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\");\n        blockhash = fresh.blockhash;\n        lastValidBlockHeight = fresh.lastValidBlockHeight;\n      }\n      \n      if (!preservesExternalSignature) {\n        transaction.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\n      }\n\n      // (4) Call wallet's sendTransaction\n      const signature = await sendTransaction(transaction);\n      console.log(`[coinflip] tx sent (attempt ${attempt}/${MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS}): ${signature}`);\n\n      // (5) Confirm with abort timeout\n      const controller = new AbortController();\n      const timeout = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 30_000);\n      try {\n        await connection.confirmTransaction(\n          { signature, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight, abortSignal: controller.signal },\n          \"confirmed\",\n        );\n        // Success\n        await refreshBalance();\n        return signature;\n      } catch (confirmErr) {\n        const msg = confirmErr instanceof Error ? confirmErr.message : String(confirmErr);\n        const isExpired = msg.includes(\"expired\") || msg.includes(\"block height exceeded\");\n        const isAborted = msg.includes(\"aborted\");\n\n        if ((isExpired || isAborted) && attempt < MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS) {\n          // Check if tx actually landed despite confirm failure\n          try {\n            const status = await connection.getSignatureStatus(signature);\n            if (\n              status.value?.confirmationStatus === \"confirmed\" ||\n              status.value?.confirmationStatus === \"finalized\"\n            ) {\n              console.log(`[coinflip] tx ${signature} confirmed via fallback status check`);\n              await refreshBalance();\n              return signature;\n            }\n          } catch {\n            // Status check failed — fall through to retry\n          }\n          console.warn(`[coinflip] tx dropped/expired on attempt ${attempt}, retrying...`);\n          continue;\n        }\n        throw confirmErr;\n      } finally {\n        clearTimeout(timeout);\n      }\n    }\n\n    throw new Error(\"Transaction failed after max retry attempts\");\n  },\n  [connection, sendTransaction, refreshBalance],\n);\n```\n\n**Critical insights:**\n- **Detects backend-signed TX**: Checks for existing signatures + pinned blockhash\n- **Pre-flight simulation**: Catches logic errors early (before wallet prompt)\n- **Retry logic**: 3 attempts for fresh TX (devnet drops), 1 for backend TX (already committed)\n- **Fallback confirmation**: If WebSocket drops, checks RPC for actual status\n- **Balance refresh**: Always refreshes balance after confirmed send\n- **Error state**: Simulation errors are fatal; confirmation timeouts/expirations are retriable\n\n---\n\n### **4. How Transactions Are Used in Lifecycle**\n\n#### Create Match Flow\nLocation: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:584`\n\n```typescript\nconst createMatch = useCallback(async () => {\n  if (!connected || !publicKey) {\n    setError(\"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\");\n    return;\n  }\n  if (!wagerAmount || !selectedSide) {\n    setError(\"Select wager amount and side first.\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Ensure authenticated\n  if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken) {\n    try {\n      await authenticate();\n    } catch {\n      setError(\"Authentication required. Please approve the sign-in message.\");\n      return;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Read fresh token from store (closure may be stale)\n  const token = accessToken ?? getAccessToken();\n  if (!token) {\n    setError(\"Authentication failed. Please try again.\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  setCreating(true);\n  setError(null);\n  setLastSettleSignature(null);\n  try {\n    logLife(\"createMatch: building tx\", { amount: wagerAmount, side: selectedSide });\n    const { transaction, matchPda } = await buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n      publicKey,\n      wagerAmount,\n      selectedSide,\n      token,\n    );\n\n    logLife(\"createMatch: sending tx\", { pda: matchPda.toBase58().slice(0, 12) });\n    await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n    logLife(\"createMatch: confirmed\", { pda: matchPda.toBase58().slice(0, 12) });\n\n    dismissedMatchRef.current = null;\n\n    const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n    if (match) {\n      logLife(\"createMatch: fetched, phase=\" + match.phase);\n      setActiveMatch(match);\n    }\n\n    setSelectedSide(null);\n    refreshMatches();\n  } catch (err) {\n    // Handle 401 from backend: attempt refresh, retry once\n    if (err instanceof BackendRequestError && err.status === 401) {\n      try {\n        await authenticate();\n        setError(\"Session refreshed. Please try again.\");\n      } catch {\n        setError(\"Session expired. Please reconnect your wallet.\");\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n    setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n  } finally {\n    setCreating(false);\n  }\n}, [connected, publicKey, wagerAmount, selectedSide, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches, isAuthenticated, accessToken, authenticate]);\n```\n\n#### Join Match Flow\nLocation: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:655`\n\n```typescript\nconst joinMatch = useCallback(\n  async (matchId: string) => {\n    if (!connected || !publicKey) {\n      setError(\"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setJoining(true);\n    setJoiningMatchId(matchId);\n    setError(null);\n    setLastSettleSignature(null);\n    try {\n      const matchPda = new PublicKey(matchId);\n      const existingMatch = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n      if (!existingMatch) {\n        setError(\"Match not found. It may have been cancelled.\");\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const transaction = await buildJoinMatchTx(\n        connection,\n        publicKey,\n        matchPda\n      );\n\n      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n\n      dismissedMatchRef.current = null;\n\n      const updated = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n      if (updated) {\n        if (updated.phase === \"ready\") {\n          // Start countdown → flip sequence\n          // ... animation orchestration code ...\n        } else {\n          setActiveMatch(updated);\n        }\n      }\n\n      refreshMatches();\n    } catch (err) {\n      setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n    } finally {\n      setJoining(false);\n      setJoiningMatchId(null);\n    }\n  },\n  [connected, publicKey, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. Error Handling Pattern**\n\nLocation: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:42`\n\nComprehensive error parsing function:\n\n```typescript\nfunction parseTransactionError(err: unknown): string {\n  if (err instanceof BackendRequestError) {\n    if (err.status === 401) {\n      return \"Backend authentication failed. Please approve message signing and try again.\";\n    }\n    if (err.status === 409) {\n      return \"Match creation failed — please retry.\";\n    }\n    if (err.status === 429) {\n      return \"Too many create attempts. Please wait a moment and try again.\";\n    }\n    return err.message;\n  }\n\n  const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n\n  // Wallet not connected\n  if (msg.includes(\"Wallet not connected\") || msg.includes(\"WalletNotConnectedError\")) {\n    return \"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\";\n  }\n\n  // User rejected\n  if (msg.includes(\"User rejected\") || msg.includes(\"Transaction cancelled\")) {\n    return \"Transaction cancelled by user.\";\n  }\n\n  // Insufficient funds\n  if (msg.includes(\"insufficient lamports\") || msg.includes(\"Insufficient funds\") || msg.includes(\"0x1\")) {\n    return \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\";\n  }\n\n  // Account already in use (match already exists)\n  if (msg.includes(\"already in use\")) {\n    return \"You already have an active match. Cancel it before creating a new one.\";\n  }\n\n  // Network / RPC errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"Failed to fetch\") || msg.includes(\"NetworkError\") || msg.includes(\"ECONNREFUSED\")) {\n    return \"Network error. Please check your connection and try again.\";\n  }\n\n  // Anchor program errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"InvalidPhase\")) {\n    return \"This match is no longer available.\";\n  }\n  if (msg.includes(\"CannotJoinOwnMatch\")) {\n    return \"You cannot join your own match.\";\n  }\n\n  // Simulation / preflight failures\n  if (msg.includes(\"Simulation failed\") || msg.includes(\"Transaction simulation failed\")) {\n    return \"Transaction simulation failed. The match may no longer be available.\";\n  }\n\n  // Blockhash expiry\n  if (msg.includes(\"blockhash not found\") || msg.includes(\"Blockhash not found\")) {\n    return \"Transaction expired. Please try again.\";\n  }\n\n  // Generic fallback\n  console.error(\"[coinflip] unhandled transaction error:\", err);\n  return `Transaction failed: ${msg.length > 100 ? msg.slice(0, 100) + \"...\" : msg}`;\n}\n```\n\n**Error display mechanism:**\n- `error` state lives in context\n- **Not displayed via toasts** (code shows `setError` calls, but no toast integration shown)\n- Must be integrated into UI components (likely via context consumer or custom hook)\n- Context provides `clearError()` to dismiss\n\n---\n\n### **6. Authentication Pattern (Session Management)**\n\nLocation: `/packages/wallet/src/context.ts` + `context/SessionContext.tsx`\n\nTwo-stage auth:\n\n**Stage 1: Challenge-Response (Sign Once)**\n```typescript\nconst authenticate = useCallback(async () => {\n  if (!connected || !publicKey || !signMessage) {\n    throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected or does not support message signing\");\n  }\n\n  setIsAuthenticating(true);\n  try {\n    const wallet = publicKey.toBase58();\n\n    // 1. Request human-readable challenge\n    const challenge = await requestChallenge(wallet);\n\n    // 2. Check expiry\n    if (new Date(challenge.expiresAt).getTime() < Date.now()) {\n      throw new Error(\"Challenge expired before signing\");\n    }\n\n    // 3. Sign with wallet (message signing, NOT transaction signing)\n    const messageBytes = new TextEncoder().encode(challenge.message);\n    const signatureBytes = await signMessage(messageBytes);\n    const signature = bs58.encode(signatureBytes);\n\n    // 4. Verify with backend → get JWT tokens\n    const result = await verifyChallenge(challenge.nonce, wallet, signature);\n\n    // 5. Store tokens\n    setAccessToken(result.accessToken, result.accessExpiresAt);\n    setPersistedSession({\n      wallet,\n      cluster: \"devnet\",\n      refreshToken: result.refreshToken,\n      refreshExpiresAt: result.refreshExpiresAt,\n    });\n\n    setIsAuthenticated(true);\n    scheduleRefresh();\n    return result.accessToken;\n  } catch (err) {\n    clearPersistedSession();\n    setIsAuthenticated(false);\n    throw err;\n  } finally {\n    setIsAuthenticating(false);\n  }\n}, [connected, publicKey, signMessage, scheduleRefresh]);\n```\n\n**Stage 2: JWT Bearer Tokens**\n- All requests use `Authorization: Bearer ${accessToken}` header\n- Backend validates JWT on each request\n- Auto-refresh 5 min before expiry using `refreshToken`\n- If refresh fails, session is cleared and user must re-authenticate\n\n---\n\n### **7. Optimistic Updates**\n\nLocated: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx` throughout\n\nPattern:\n1. **After successful TX confirmation**:\n   - Fetch updated match state from on-chain\n   - Update `activeMatch` with fresh data\n   - Clear form state (e.g., `setSelectedSide(null)`)\n   - Refresh lobby lists (`refreshMatches()`)\n\n2. **During TX confirmation**:\n   - Loading flags: `creating`, `joining` prevent double-submit\n   - UI shows \"Creating...\" / \"Joining...\" buttons\n\n3. **No speculative writes** to state during TX building — only after confirmation\n\nExample:\n```typescript\nconst transaction = await buildJoinMatchTx(connection, publicKey, matchPda);\nawait sendAndConfirm(transaction);  // Wait for confirmation\n\n// Then fetch updated state\nconst updated = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\nif (updated) {\n  setActiveMatch(updated);  // Optimistic update after confirm\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **8. Key Anchor Patterns**\n\n**Program Instance (Read-Only)**\n```typescript\nconst program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);  // No wallet needed for queries\nconst account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(pda);\n```\n\n**Instruction Building**\n```typescript\nconst ix = await program.methods\n  .joinMatch()\n  .accountsStrict({\n    opponent,\n    coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n    config: configPda,\n    systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n  })\n  .instruction();\n```\n\n**IDL Usage**\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nconst program = new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n```\n\n**Transaction Finalization**\n```typescript\nconst tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\ntx.feePayer = payer;\ntx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n```\n\n---\n\n### **9. Constants & Configuration**\n\n**Program IDs:**\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n```\n\n**Phase Constants:**\n```typescript\nconst PHASE_WAITING = 0;\nconst PHASE_LOCKED = 1;\nconst PHASE_SETTLED = 2;\nconst PHASE_REFUNDED = 3;\n```\n\n**Backend URL:**\n```typescript\nconst FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n```\n\n---\n\n### **10. Settlement & Verification**\n\n**Commit-Reveal Cryptography:**\n```typescript\n// Generate secret on create\nconst secret = new Uint8Array(32);\ncrypto.getRandomValues(secret);\n\n// Compute commitment\nconst commitment = await sha256(secret);\n```\n\n**Event Verification** (after settlement):\n```typescript\nexport async function verifyMatch(\n  connection: Connection,\n  settleTxSignature: string\n): Promise<VerificationResult> {\n  const tx = await connection.getTransaction(settleTxSignature, {\n    commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    maxSupportedTransactionVersion: 0,\n  });\n\n  const coder = new BorshCoder(CoinflipIDL as Idl);\n  const eventParser = new EventParser(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, coder);\n\n  for (const event of eventParser.parseLogs(tx.meta.logMessages)) {\n    if (event.name === \"matchSettled\") {\n      // Verify commitment: SHA256(secret) == commitment\n      const computedCommitment = await sha256(secretBytes);\n      const commitmentValid = bytesToHex(computedCommitment) === bytesToHex(commitmentBytes);\n      \n      // Verify result: result_hash[0] % 2 == result_side\n      const resultValid = resultHashBytes[0] % 2 === resultSide;\n      \n      return { verified: commitmentValid && resultValid && winnerIsValid, ... };\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Summary: The Replication Checklist for CloseCall**\n\nTo replicate this pattern for closecall, you need:\n\n1. ✅ **Chain utility file** (`utils/chain.ts`):\n   - `buildBackendCreateMatchTx()` (backend constructs, you decode)\n   - `buildJoinMatchTx()` (frontend builds using Anchor)\n   - `buildCancelMatchTx()`, `buildTimeoutRefundTx()` as needed\n   - `fetchMatch()`, `fetchAllMatches()` queries\n   - Error class: `BackendRequestError`\n\n2. ✅ **Context provider** (`context/ClosecallContext.tsx`):\n   - Match state: `activeMatch`, `openMatches`, `wagerAmount`, `selectedOutcome`\n   - Loading states: `creating`, `joining`, `loading`\n   - Error state: `error`, `clearError()`\n   - Actions: `createMatch()`, `joinMatch()`, `cancelMatch()`, etc.\n   - `sendAndConfirm()` helper with retry logic + balance refresh\n   - Settlement polling + WebSocket event watching\n\n3. ✅ **Types** (`types.ts`):\n   - `UIMatch` with all on-chain state mapped to UI fields\n   - `ClosecallPhase` enum (created → locked → settled → etc.)\n\n4. ✅ **Error parsing**:\n   - User-friendly messages for all Solana/Anchor errors\n   - Special handling for 401 (auth refresh), 409 (race), 429 (rate limit)\n\n5. ✅ **Authentication**:\n   - Use `SessionContext` for JWT tokens (already exists in platform)\n   - Pass `accessToken` to backend create endpoint\n\n6. ✅ **Components** (use context via `useCoinflip()` pattern):\n   - Render `activeMatch` with phase-specific UI\n   - Render `openMatches` list (with filtering/sorting)\n   - Display `error` state (no toast shown in code, but UI integration needed)\n\n---\n\n### **All File Paths (Absolute)**\n\nKey reference files for closecall implementation:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — **THE master file** (1000 lines, all patterns)\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — TX building functions (612 lines)\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — UIMatch shape (54 lines)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts` — Wallet hook (12 lines)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx` — Wallet bridge (120 lines)\n6. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx` — Auth + JWT management (230+ lines)\n7. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` — UI integration example (434 lines)\n8. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.ts` — IDL shape reference (generated, read-only)\n\n---\n\nThis is the **canonical, production pattern** used in coinflip. It handles wallet abstraction, backend coordination, transaction lifecycle, error recovery, and settlement verification. Replicate this structure exactly for closecall (adjusting types/instructions for your game rules)."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a203ab741a0c3095b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 89792\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 114532</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69ec7f4b-ea2c-48d6-9a60-da2ab1703b1a","uuid":"d82dd2bc-3e6a-4c23-82f5-d96f384682d2","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore how coinflip handles wallet transaction building and signing for placing bets. I need to understand the exact pattern to replicate for closecall.\n\nLook at:\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/` - find how placeBet/createMatch/joinMatch builds and sends transactions\n2. How `useWallet()` is used for signing\n3. How transactions are built using the IDL from `@rng-utopia/anchor-client`\n4. How errors are handled (toasts, insufficient balance, etc.)\n5. How optimistic updates work after successful tx\n\nThoroughness: very thorough. Read the full context files.","agentId":"a203ab741a0c3095b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile a detailed technical report.\n\n## Comprehensive Exploration Report: Coinflip Wallet Transaction Building & Signing Pattern\n\nI've completed a very thorough analysis of how coinflip handles wallet transaction building, signing, and error handling. Here's the complete pattern you should replicate for closecall:\n\n---\n\n### **Architecture Overview**\n\nThe pattern follows **contract-first design**: transaction building is split between **backend (trust-critical)** and **frontend (UI/UX)**.\n\n**Key Files:**\n- **Backend TX building**: `utils/chain.ts` (`buildBackendCreateMatchTx`, `buildJoinMatchTx`, etc.)\n- **State management**: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx` (all transaction orchestration + error handling)\n- **Wallet integration**: `@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` → `useWallet()` hook\n- **IDL definitions**: `@rng-utopia/anchor-client` → `CoinflipIDL` (read-only, pre-compiled)\n\n---\n\n### **1. Wallet Integration Pattern**\n\n#### The `useWallet()` Hook\nLocated: `/packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts`\n\n```typescript\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(WalletContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useWallet must be used within a WalletProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**Returns** (`WalletContextValue`):\n```typescript\n{\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  getBalance?: () => number;        // mock mode only\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void;  // mock mode only\n}\n```\n\n#### Real Wallet Provider\nLocated: `/packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx`\n\nBridges `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` hooks to custom `WalletContext`:\n\n```typescript\nconst sendTransaction = useCallback(\n  async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n    if (!adapter.publicKey) {\n      throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected\");\n    }\n    const signature = await adapter.sendTransaction(transaction, connection);\n    return signature;\n  },\n  [adapter, connection],\n);\n```\n\n**Critical**: `sendTransaction` is a **direct pass-through** to the wallet adapter. It:\n- Does NOT sign transactions (wallet does that)\n- Does NOT set fee payers (caller does that)\n- Does NOT manage blockhashes (caller does that)\n- Simply returns the signature after broadcast\n\n---\n\n### **2. Transaction Building Pattern (Backend-First)**\n\n#### Create Match (Backend-Generated TX)\nLocation: `/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts:462`\n\n```typescript\nexport async function buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n  creator: PublicKey,\n  amountSol: number,\n  side: CoinSide,\n  accessToken: string,\n): Promise<{ transaction: Transaction; matchPda: PublicKey; commitment: string }> {\n  const payload = {\n    wallet: creator.toBase58(),\n    amountLamports: Math.round(amountSol * 1e9),\n    side: COIN_SIDE_VALUES[side],  // { heads: 0, tails: 1 }\n  };\n\n  const response = await fetch(getFairnessBackendCreateUrl(), {\n    method: \"POST\",\n    headers: {\n      \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n      \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${accessToken}`,  // JWT from SessionContext\n    },\n    body: JSON.stringify(payload),\n  });\n\n  const json = await parseBackendResponse<BackendCreateMatchResponse>(response);\n\n  return {\n    transaction: (() => {\n      const transaction = Transaction.from(Buffer.from(json.transaction, \"base64\"));\n      transaction.lastValidBlockHeight = json.lastValidBlockHeight;\n      return transaction;\n    })(),\n    matchPda: new PublicKey(json.matchPda),\n    commitment: json.commitment,\n  };\n}\n```\n\n**Key details:**\n- Backend constructs the raw transaction (contains all instructions)\n- Backend sends it **base64-encoded** with **pinned blockhash + lastValidBlockHeight**\n- Frontend decodes and reconstructs `Transaction` object\n- **Do NOT modify the transaction** — server already signed its parts\n- **Critical**: `transaction.lastValidBlockHeight` must be preserved (used later for confirmation logic)\n\n#### Join/Cancel/Timeout Refund (Frontend-Built TX)\nLocation: `/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts:498–574`\n\n```typescript\nexport async function buildJoinMatchTx(\n  connection: Connection,\n  opponent: PublicKey,\n  matchPda: PublicKey\n): Promise<Transaction> {\n  const program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);\n  const [configPda] = getConfigPda();\n\n  const ix = await program.methods\n    .joinMatch()\n    .accountsStrict({\n      opponent,\n      coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n      config: configPda,\n      systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n    })\n    .instruction();\n\n  const tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\n  tx.feePayer = opponent;\n  tx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n\n  return tx;\n}\n```\n\n**Pattern:**\n1. Create `Program` instance using **read-only provider** (no wallet needed):\n   ```typescript\n   function getCoinflipProgram(connection: Connection): Program<Coinflip> {\n     const provider = new AnchorProvider(\n       connection,\n       {} as AnchorProvider[\"wallet\"],\n       { commitment: \"confirmed\" }\n     );\n     return new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. Build instruction via Anchor's `program.methods.<instruction>(args).accountsStrict({...}).instruction()`\n3. Create blank `Transaction()` and add the instruction\n4. Set `tx.feePayer = payer` (the account sending the tx)\n5. Fetch fresh blockhash and set `tx.recentBlockhash`\n6. Return (caller will sign + send)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Transaction Signing & Sending Pattern**\n\nLocated: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:186`\n\nThe **`sendAndConfirm` function** orchestrates the entire flow:\n\n```typescript\nconst sendAndConfirm = useCallback(\n  async (transaction: Transaction): Promise<string> => {\n    // (1) Detect if backend pre-signed the transaction\n    const hasPartialSignatures = transaction.signatures.some(\n      (entry) => entry.signature !== null\n    );\n    const preservesExternalSignature =\n      hasPartialSignatures &&\n      typeof transaction.recentBlockhash === \"string\";\n    const hasPinnedBlockhash =\n      preservesExternalSignature &&\n      typeof transaction.lastValidBlockHeight === \"number\";\n\n    if (preservesExternalSignature && !hasPinnedBlockhash) {\n      throw new Error(\n        \"Backend transaction is missing lastValidBlockHeight. Refusing to send with an incomplete confirmation contract.\",\n      );\n    }\n\n    // (2) Pre-flight simulation (unsigned, best-effort)\n    let cachedBlockhash: string | undefined;\n    let cachedHeight: number | undefined;\n    try {\n      if (!preservesExternalSignature) {\n        const { blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight } =\n          await connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\");\n        cachedBlockhash = blockhash;\n        cachedHeight = lastValidBlockHeight;\n        transaction.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\n      }\n\n      const simResult = await connection.simulateTransaction(transaction);\n      if (simResult.value.err) {\n        console.error(\"[coinflip] simulation failed BEFORE wallet send:\", \n          JSON.stringify(simResult.value.err));\n        if (simResult.value.logs) {\n          console.error(\"[coinflip] simulation logs:\\n\" + simResult.value.logs.join(\"\\n\"));\n        }\n        const err = simResult.value.err;\n        if (typeof err === \"object\" && err !== null && \"InstructionError\" in err) {\n          throw new Error(`Transaction will fail: ${JSON.stringify(err)}`);\n        }\n      }\n    } catch (simErr) {\n      if (simErr instanceof Error && simErr.message.startsWith(\"Transaction will fail:\")) {\n        throw simErr;\n      }\n      console.error(\"[coinflip] simulation RPC error:\", simErr);\n    }\n\n    // (3) Send with retry logic (max 3 times for fresh TX, 1 time for backend TX)\n    const MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS = preservesExternalSignature ? 1 : 3;\n    for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS; attempt++) {\n      let blockhash: string;\n      let lastValidBlockHeight: number;\n      \n      if (preservesExternalSignature) {\n        // Reuse backend's pinned blockhash (already set in transaction)\n        blockhash = transaction.recentBlockhash!;\n        lastValidBlockHeight = transaction.lastValidBlockHeight ?? 0;\n      } else if (attempt === 1 && cachedBlockhash && cachedHeight) {\n        // Reuse simulation blockhash for first attempt (saves an RPC call)\n        blockhash = cachedBlockhash;\n        lastValidBlockHeight = cachedHeight;\n      } else {\n        // Fresh blockhash for retries\n        const fresh = await connection.getLatestBlockhash(\"confirmed\");\n        blockhash = fresh.blockhash;\n        lastValidBlockHeight = fresh.lastValidBlockHeight;\n      }\n      \n      if (!preservesExternalSignature) {\n        transaction.recentBlockhash = blockhash;\n      }\n\n      // (4) Call wallet's sendTransaction\n      const signature = await sendTransaction(transaction);\n      console.log(`[coinflip] tx sent (attempt ${attempt}/${MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS}): ${signature}`);\n\n      // (5) Confirm with abort timeout\n      const controller = new AbortController();\n      const timeout = setTimeout(() => controller.abort(), 30_000);\n      try {\n        await connection.confirmTransaction(\n          { signature, blockhash, lastValidBlockHeight, abortSignal: controller.signal },\n          \"confirmed\",\n        );\n        // Success\n        await refreshBalance();\n        return signature;\n      } catch (confirmErr) {\n        const msg = confirmErr instanceof Error ? confirmErr.message : String(confirmErr);\n        const isExpired = msg.includes(\"expired\") || msg.includes(\"block height exceeded\");\n        const isAborted = msg.includes(\"aborted\");\n\n        if ((isExpired || isAborted) && attempt < MAX_SEND_ATTEMPTS) {\n          // Check if tx actually landed despite confirm failure\n          try {\n            const status = await connection.getSignatureStatus(signature);\n            if (\n              status.value?.confirmationStatus === \"confirmed\" ||\n              status.value?.confirmationStatus === \"finalized\"\n            ) {\n              console.log(`[coinflip] tx ${signature} confirmed via fallback status check`);\n              await refreshBalance();\n              return signature;\n            }\n          } catch {\n            // Status check failed — fall through to retry\n          }\n          console.warn(`[coinflip] tx dropped/expired on attempt ${attempt}, retrying...`);\n          continue;\n        }\n        throw confirmErr;\n      } finally {\n        clearTimeout(timeout);\n      }\n    }\n\n    throw new Error(\"Transaction failed after max retry attempts\");\n  },\n  [connection, sendTransaction, refreshBalance],\n);\n```\n\n**Critical insights:**\n- **Detects backend-signed TX**: Checks for existing signatures + pinned blockhash\n- **Pre-flight simulation**: Catches logic errors early (before wallet prompt)\n- **Retry logic**: 3 attempts for fresh TX (devnet drops), 1 for backend TX (already committed)\n- **Fallback confirmation**: If WebSocket drops, checks RPC for actual status\n- **Balance refresh**: Always refreshes balance after confirmed send\n- **Error state**: Simulation errors are fatal; confirmation timeouts/expirations are retriable\n\n---\n\n### **4. How Transactions Are Used in Lifecycle**\n\n#### Create Match Flow\nLocation: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:584`\n\n```typescript\nconst createMatch = useCallback(async () => {\n  if (!connected || !publicKey) {\n    setError(\"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\");\n    return;\n  }\n  if (!wagerAmount || !selectedSide) {\n    setError(\"Select wager amount and side first.\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Ensure authenticated\n  if (!isAuthenticated || !accessToken) {\n    try {\n      await authenticate();\n    } catch {\n      setError(\"Authentication required. Please approve the sign-in message.\");\n      return;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Read fresh token from store (closure may be stale)\n  const token = accessToken ?? getAccessToken();\n  if (!token) {\n    setError(\"Authentication failed. Please try again.\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  setCreating(true);\n  setError(null);\n  setLastSettleSignature(null);\n  try {\n    logLife(\"createMatch: building tx\", { amount: wagerAmount, side: selectedSide });\n    const { transaction, matchPda } = await buildBackendCreateMatchTx(\n      publicKey,\n      wagerAmount,\n      selectedSide,\n      token,\n    );\n\n    logLife(\"createMatch: sending tx\", { pda: matchPda.toBase58().slice(0, 12) });\n    await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n    logLife(\"createMatch: confirmed\", { pda: matchPda.toBase58().slice(0, 12) });\n\n    dismissedMatchRef.current = null;\n\n    const match = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n    if (match) {\n      logLife(\"createMatch: fetched, phase=\" + match.phase);\n      setActiveMatch(match);\n    }\n\n    setSelectedSide(null);\n    refreshMatches();\n  } catch (err) {\n    // Handle 401 from backend: attempt refresh, retry once\n    if (err instanceof BackendRequestError && err.status === 401) {\n      try {\n        await authenticate();\n        setError(\"Session refreshed. Please try again.\");\n      } catch {\n        setError(\"Session expired. Please reconnect your wallet.\");\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n    setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n  } finally {\n    setCreating(false);\n  }\n}, [connected, publicKey, wagerAmount, selectedSide, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches, isAuthenticated, accessToken, authenticate]);\n```\n\n#### Join Match Flow\nLocation: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:655`\n\n```typescript\nconst joinMatch = useCallback(\n  async (matchId: string) => {\n    if (!connected || !publicKey) {\n      setError(\"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\");\n      return;\n    }\n\n    setJoining(true);\n    setJoiningMatchId(matchId);\n    setError(null);\n    setLastSettleSignature(null);\n    try {\n      const matchPda = new PublicKey(matchId);\n      const existingMatch = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n      if (!existingMatch) {\n        setError(\"Match not found. It may have been cancelled.\");\n        return;\n      }\n\n      const transaction = await buildJoinMatchTx(\n        connection,\n        publicKey,\n        matchPda\n      );\n\n      await sendAndConfirm(transaction);\n\n      dismissedMatchRef.current = null;\n\n      const updated = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\n      if (updated) {\n        if (updated.phase === \"ready\") {\n          // Start countdown → flip sequence\n          // ... animation orchestration code ...\n        } else {\n          setActiveMatch(updated);\n        }\n      }\n\n      refreshMatches();\n    } catch (err) {\n      setError(parseTransactionError(err));\n    } finally {\n      setJoining(false);\n      setJoiningMatchId(null);\n    }\n  },\n  [connected, publicKey, connection, sendAndConfirm, refreshMatches]\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### **5. Error Handling Pattern**\n\nLocation: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx:42`\n\nComprehensive error parsing function:\n\n```typescript\nfunction parseTransactionError(err: unknown): string {\n  if (err instanceof BackendRequestError) {\n    if (err.status === 401) {\n      return \"Backend authentication failed. Please approve message signing and try again.\";\n    }\n    if (err.status === 409) {\n      return \"Match creation failed — please retry.\";\n    }\n    if (err.status === 429) {\n      return \"Too many create attempts. Please wait a moment and try again.\";\n    }\n    return err.message;\n  }\n\n  const msg = err instanceof Error ? err.message : String(err);\n\n  // Wallet not connected\n  if (msg.includes(\"Wallet not connected\") || msg.includes(\"WalletNotConnectedError\")) {\n    return \"Wallet not connected. Please connect your wallet first.\";\n  }\n\n  // User rejected\n  if (msg.includes(\"User rejected\") || msg.includes(\"Transaction cancelled\")) {\n    return \"Transaction cancelled by user.\";\n  }\n\n  // Insufficient funds\n  if (msg.includes(\"insufficient lamports\") || msg.includes(\"Insufficient funds\") || msg.includes(\"0x1\")) {\n    return \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\";\n  }\n\n  // Account already in use (match already exists)\n  if (msg.includes(\"already in use\")) {\n    return \"You already have an active match. Cancel it before creating a new one.\";\n  }\n\n  // Network / RPC errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"Failed to fetch\") || msg.includes(\"NetworkError\") || msg.includes(\"ECONNREFUSED\")) {\n    return \"Network error. Please check your connection and try again.\";\n  }\n\n  // Anchor program errors\n  if (msg.includes(\"InvalidPhase\")) {\n    return \"This match is no longer available.\";\n  }\n  if (msg.includes(\"CannotJoinOwnMatch\")) {\n    return \"You cannot join your own match.\";\n  }\n\n  // Simulation / preflight failures\n  if (msg.includes(\"Simulation failed\") || msg.includes(\"Transaction simulation failed\")) {\n    return \"Transaction simulation failed. The match may no longer be available.\";\n  }\n\n  // Blockhash expiry\n  if (msg.includes(\"blockhash not found\") || msg.includes(\"Blockhash not found\")) {\n    return \"Transaction expired. Please try again.\";\n  }\n\n  // Generic fallback\n  console.error(\"[coinflip] unhandled transaction error:\", err);\n  return `Transaction failed: ${msg.length > 100 ? msg.slice(0, 100) + \"...\" : msg}`;\n}\n```\n\n**Error display mechanism:**\n- `error` state lives in context\n- **Not displayed via toasts** (code shows `setError` calls, but no toast integration shown)\n- Must be integrated into UI components (likely via context consumer or custom hook)\n- Context provides `clearError()` to dismiss\n\n---\n\n### **6. Authentication Pattern (Session Management)**\n\nLocation: `/packages/wallet/src/context.ts` + `context/SessionContext.tsx`\n\nTwo-stage auth:\n\n**Stage 1: Challenge-Response (Sign Once)**\n```typescript\nconst authenticate = useCallback(async () => {\n  if (!connected || !publicKey || !signMessage) {\n    throw new Error(\"Wallet not connected or does not support message signing\");\n  }\n\n  setIsAuthenticating(true);\n  try {\n    const wallet = publicKey.toBase58();\n\n    // 1. Request human-readable challenge\n    const challenge = await requestChallenge(wallet);\n\n    // 2. Check expiry\n    if (new Date(challenge.expiresAt).getTime() < Date.now()) {\n      throw new Error(\"Challenge expired before signing\");\n    }\n\n    // 3. Sign with wallet (message signing, NOT transaction signing)\n    const messageBytes = new TextEncoder().encode(challenge.message);\n    const signatureBytes = await signMessage(messageBytes);\n    const signature = bs58.encode(signatureBytes);\n\n    // 4. Verify with backend → get JWT tokens\n    const result = await verifyChallenge(challenge.nonce, wallet, signature);\n\n    // 5. Store tokens\n    setAccessToken(result.accessToken, result.accessExpiresAt);\n    setPersistedSession({\n      wallet,\n      cluster: \"devnet\",\n      refreshToken: result.refreshToken,\n      refreshExpiresAt: result.refreshExpiresAt,\n    });\n\n    setIsAuthenticated(true);\n    scheduleRefresh();\n    return result.accessToken;\n  } catch (err) {\n    clearPersistedSession();\n    setIsAuthenticated(false);\n    throw err;\n  } finally {\n    setIsAuthenticating(false);\n  }\n}, [connected, publicKey, signMessage, scheduleRefresh]);\n```\n\n**Stage 2: JWT Bearer Tokens**\n- All requests use `Authorization: Bearer ${accessToken}` header\n- Backend validates JWT on each request\n- Auto-refresh 5 min before expiry using `refreshToken`\n- If refresh fails, session is cleared and user must re-authenticate\n\n---\n\n### **7. Optimistic Updates**\n\nLocated: `context/CoinflipContext.tsx` throughout\n\nPattern:\n1. **After successful TX confirmation**:\n   - Fetch updated match state from on-chain\n   - Update `activeMatch` with fresh data\n   - Clear form state (e.g., `setSelectedSide(null)`)\n   - Refresh lobby lists (`refreshMatches()`)\n\n2. **During TX confirmation**:\n   - Loading flags: `creating`, `joining` prevent double-submit\n   - UI shows \"Creating...\" / \"Joining...\" buttons\n\n3. **No speculative writes** to state during TX building — only after confirmation\n\nExample:\n```typescript\nconst transaction = await buildJoinMatchTx(connection, publicKey, matchPda);\nawait sendAndConfirm(transaction);  // Wait for confirmation\n\n// Then fetch updated state\nconst updated = await fetchMatch(connection, matchPda);\nif (updated) {\n  setActiveMatch(updated);  // Optimistic update after confirm\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **8. Key Anchor Patterns**\n\n**Program Instance (Read-Only)**\n```typescript\nconst program = getCoinflipProgram(connection);  // No wallet needed for queries\nconst account = await program.account.coinflipMatch.fetch(pda);\n```\n\n**Instruction Building**\n```typescript\nconst ix = await program.methods\n  .joinMatch()\n  .accountsStrict({\n    opponent,\n    coinflipMatch: matchPda,\n    config: configPda,\n    systemProgram: SystemProgram.programId,\n  })\n  .instruction();\n```\n\n**IDL Usage**\n```typescript\nimport { CoinflipIDL, type Coinflip } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n\nconst program = new Program(CoinflipIDL as Idl as Coinflip, provider);\n```\n\n**Transaction Finalization**\n```typescript\nconst tx = new Transaction().add(ix);\ntx.feePayer = payer;\ntx.recentBlockhash = (await connection.getLatestBlockhash()).blockhash;\n```\n\n---\n\n### **9. Constants & Configuration**\n\n**Program IDs:**\n```typescript\nexport const COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID = new PublicKey(\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID ?? CoinflipIDL.address\n);\n```\n\n**Phase Constants:**\n```typescript\nconst PHASE_WAITING = 0;\nconst PHASE_LOCKED = 1;\nconst PHASE_SETTLED = 2;\nconst PHASE_REFUNDED = 3;\n```\n\n**Backend URL:**\n```typescript\nconst FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL = (\n  (import.meta as unknown as { env: Record<string, string | undefined> }).env\n    .VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL ?? \"http://127.0.0.1:3100\"\n).replace(/\\/$/, \"\");\n```\n\n---\n\n### **10. Settlement & Verification**\n\n**Commit-Reveal Cryptography:**\n```typescript\n// Generate secret on create\nconst secret = new Uint8Array(32);\ncrypto.getRandomValues(secret);\n\n// Compute commitment\nconst commitment = await sha256(secret);\n```\n\n**Event Verification** (after settlement):\n```typescript\nexport async function verifyMatch(\n  connection: Connection,\n  settleTxSignature: string\n): Promise<VerificationResult> {\n  const tx = await connection.getTransaction(settleTxSignature, {\n    commitment: \"confirmed\",\n    maxSupportedTransactionVersion: 0,\n  });\n\n  const coder = new BorshCoder(CoinflipIDL as Idl);\n  const eventParser = new EventParser(COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID, coder);\n\n  for (const event of eventParser.parseLogs(tx.meta.logMessages)) {\n    if (event.name === \"matchSettled\") {\n      // Verify commitment: SHA256(secret) == commitment\n      const computedCommitment = await sha256(secretBytes);\n      const commitmentValid = bytesToHex(computedCommitment) === bytesToHex(commitmentBytes);\n      \n      // Verify result: result_hash[0] % 2 == result_side\n      const resultValid = resultHashBytes[0] % 2 === resultSide;\n      \n      return { verified: commitmentValid && resultValid && winnerIsValid, ... };\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Summary: The Replication Checklist for CloseCall**\n\nTo replicate this pattern for closecall, you need:\n\n1. ✅ **Chain utility file** (`utils/chain.ts`):\n   - `buildBackendCreateMatchTx()` (backend constructs, you decode)\n   - `buildJoinMatchTx()` (frontend builds using Anchor)\n   - `buildCancelMatchTx()`, `buildTimeoutRefundTx()` as needed\n   - `fetchMatch()`, `fetchAllMatches()` queries\n   - Error class: `BackendRequestError`\n\n2. ✅ **Context provider** (`context/ClosecallContext.tsx`):\n   - Match state: `activeMatch`, `openMatches`, `wagerAmount`, `selectedOutcome`\n   - Loading states: `creating`, `joining`, `loading`\n   - Error state: `error`, `clearError()`\n   - Actions: `createMatch()`, `joinMatch()`, `cancelMatch()`, etc.\n   - `sendAndConfirm()` helper with retry logic + balance refresh\n   - Settlement polling + WebSocket event watching\n\n3. ✅ **Types** (`types.ts`):\n   - `UIMatch` with all on-chain state mapped to UI fields\n   - `ClosecallPhase` enum (created → locked → settled → etc.)\n\n4. ✅ **Error parsing**:\n   - User-friendly messages for all Solana/Anchor errors\n   - Special handling for 401 (auth refresh), 409 (race), 429 (rate limit)\n\n5. ✅ **Authentication**:\n   - Use `SessionContext` for JWT tokens (already exists in platform)\n   - Pass `accessToken` to backend create endpoint\n\n6. ✅ **Components** (use context via `useCoinflip()` pattern):\n   - Render `activeMatch` with phase-specific UI\n   - Render `openMatches` list (with filtering/sorting)\n   - Display `error` state (no toast shown in code, but UI integration needed)\n\n---\n\n### **All File Paths (Absolute)**\n\nKey reference files for closecall implementation:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — **THE master file** (1000 lines, all patterns)\n2. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/chain.ts` — TX building functions (612 lines)\n3. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — UIMatch shape (54 lines)\n4. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts` — Wallet hook (12 lines)\n5. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/src/real/RealWalletProvider.tsx` — Wallet bridge (120 lines)\n6. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/context/SessionContext.tsx` — Auth + JWT management (230+ lines)\n7. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CoinflipPage.tsx` — UI integration example (434 lines)\n8. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.ts` — IDL shape reference (generated, read-only)\n\n---\n\nThis is the **canonical, production pattern** used in coinflip. It handles wallet abstraction, backend coordination, transaction lifecycle, error recovery, and settlement verification. Replicate this structure exactly for closecall (adjusting types/instructions for your game rules)."}],"totalDurationMs":114532,"totalTokens":89792,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2595,"cache_read_input_tokens":79735,"output_tokens":7462,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2595},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
