{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BPa8KuV9EFK7mJiiatoAcG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that `game-engine/src/closecall.ts` uses `Buffer.from()`, which in a browser build requires the node polyfill. But the `game-engine` package doesn't have the node polyfill configured. This is why the `browser.ts` export specifically excludes the closecall, coinflip, and lordofrngs modules (which use Buffer).\n\nThe coinflip code in `chain.ts` defines its own PDA functions locally and doesn't import from `game-engine` for PDA derivation. I should follow the same pattern — define the PDA helpers locally in the context file (or create a `chain.ts` utility file).\n\n\nI'll move the PDA helper functions directly into the context file to avoid the import dependency.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":278,"cache_read_input_tokens":96879,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":278},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"69ec7f4b-ea2c-48d6-9a60-da2ab1703b1a","uuid":"2828ae07-4062-42a3-acca-907bbd1725a9"}
